description.narrative: Oxfam Novib Country Office in Mozambique is the intermediary for the AGIR Programme which is a programme on governance funded by the Embassies of Sweden and the Netherlands, being implemented by Oxfam since 2010. The main objective of the programme is #to ensure active citizens and strong and vibrant civil society that influences and participates in democratic proccess contributing for more responsive governance, deepened democracy, gender equity and human rights in Mozambique#. The programme was extended for the next 6 years (2015-2020), with a budget of SEK 180 million (equivalent to Euro 18.8 million) for the first 3 years (2015-17) to be renewed for the other 3 years (2018-2020). The current phase has 4 themes: 1) monitoring of public services (health, transport, water and social protection); 2) gender and sexual and reproductive health and rights; 3) social inclusion and non-discrimination against marginalised groups (older people, PLWHA, LGBTI and women); and, 4. Extractive industry. Environment and climate change, human rights basedapproach, gender, and HIV and AIDS are mainstreamed in all 4 thematic areas. The country office has fully 13 staff that are funded by the project.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib is one of the 17 national affiliates of the Oxfam International Confederation. It started life in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Working together in confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education forall, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam established this country office to support local organizations and projects. Through this local office Oxfam Novib directly contributes towards this project’s implementation.
